This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring February as National African American History Month. The proclamation highlights the contributions and struggles of African Americans throughout American history. The theme for this year's celebration is "African Americans and the Civil War," reflecting on the 150th anniversary of the war and the African American patriots who fought for justice and equality. The proclamation acknowledges the sacrifices made by African American soldiers, as well as the support provided by black men and women in various roles during the war. It also recognizes the ongoing efforts to achieve equal opportunity and civil rights for all Americans. The proclamation calls for the observance of National African American History Month through appropriate programs and activities.